originalText.text: Small compact yet the products are very accessible when inside this place.. They serve primarily Spanish food in the hot food eatery also it is not a sit down place. The food is very tasty,,wide range of snacks. Good sandwiches made to order. Cool drinks coffee Wonderful service, overall a very wonderful place try it you're going to like it.

originalText.text: One of the better Chinese spots in the area.  The food is always fresh, delivery is quick and they remember orders.  There are more than a few Thai-style options on the menu.  This is also one of the few places that knows how to make the large, moist-style scallion pancakes.  The smaller meal sizes and appetizers are varied and just as filling as the larger combination plates.

originalText.text: Ordered food and a hour and 15min later still wasn't here so I called and canceled. She never said sorry and did not call the man and tell him not to come. I still turned the food down when he came because that's HORRIBLE service. No one should ever wait that long for a delivery. Or tell people over the phone. I'm sick and needed to eat. Unprofessional to say the least. Not ordering from here again.

Standard fare local Chinese spot. So don't expect top grade service, or ambiance. It's take out anyway. But a some things that set Ocean apart in a good way:

- the fried wings are HUGE and they cut them up standard.
- they take debit/credit cards, which is a rarity for local Chinese spots.

originalText.text: Dirty place, nasty.  But they have great tasting food. I stopped ordering from them for hygiene reasons.  Why are so many Chinese food restaurants in the hood so nasty n why are most of their workers so rude?  Why aren't government agencies doing more to fix the issues?
